name: BatchUpdateIntentsRequest
description:
The request message for [Intents.BatchUpdateIntents][google.cloud.dialogflow.v2.Intents.BatchUpdateIntents].

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The name of the agent to update or create intents in. Format: projects/<Project ID>/agent.

params.name: data.intent_batch_uri
params.description: The URI to a Google Cloud Storage file containing intents to update or create. The file format can either be a serialized proto (of IntentBatch type) or JSON object. Note: The URI must start with "gs://".

params.name: data.intent_batch_inline
params.description: The collection of intents to update or create.

params.name: data.language_code
params.description: Optional. The language of training phrases, parameters and rich messages defined in intents. If not specified, the agent's default language is used. Many languages are supported. Note: languages must be enabled in the agent before they can be used.

params.name: data.update_mask
params.description: Optional. The mask to control which fields get updated.

params.name: data.intent_view
params.description: Optional. The resource view to apply to the returned intent.
